== English ==
=== Alternative spellings ===
* open a can of whup ass
* open a can of whoop-ass
=== Etymology ===
The origin of this figurative anarchy-related phrase is presently unknown, although its usage is closely associated with the [[w:A Team|A Team]] TV program character BA Barracus ([[w:Mr. T|Mr. T]]). 
=== Idiom ===
[[Category:English idioms]]
'''Open a can of whoop ass'''
# (''slang'', ''United States English, particularly Southern'') commonly used as a good humoured threat meaning that the speaker may soon initiate the breaking loose of all hell
#*'''Example usage:''' "I'm gonna open up a can of whoop-ass on ya",
#*'''quotations:''' It has appeared in several movies including ''[[w:Bruce Almighty|Bruce Almighty]]'', ''[[w:The Waterboy|The Waterboy]]''.